Clifford Kenton SHOWERS, Appellant, v. The PRUDENTIAL INSURANCE COMPANY OF AMERICA, Appellee. No. 7647. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. March 2, 1937. Elmer McClain, of Lima, Ohio, and Edgar W. Tait, of Urbana, Ohio, for appellant. Vance Brand and G. V. Fromme, both of Urbana, Ohio, and Davis Harrison, of Indianapolis, Ind., for appellee.

Before HICKS, SIMONS, and ALLEN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

This day the appeal of Clifford Kenton Showers, appellant, is hereby docketed and dismissed at the cost of the appellant.
